    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contexed, ContextCached, FormCreatorProducer, FormUpdateProducer<D>, FilterMatcher<D>, TypeConverter<D,java.lang.Number>, Selector<DataObjectItemInput<D>>, Owner, IndexedProducer<D>, ServeDataProducer, SettableServeDataProducer, Tagged, Targetted<D>

    public class DataObjectDataProducer<D extends DataObjectDataProducer.MimeData>
extends DataObjectFactory<D>
implements SettableServeDataProducer
    A SettableServeDataProducer implemented as a database table. It is intended to be a straightforward replacement for SessionDataProducer trading off database space and overhead for memory in the user session. Note that if sessions are being persisted to the database then the SessionDataProducer will also consume database space though this will automatically be reclaimed at the end of the session. It can also be extended to provide more sophisticated access control Each item of data belongs to a single user and expires after a specified date

    spb
